This Is Where You'll Find Me

You might have a hard time getting me to sit still for any length of time. I am often looking for the next adventure, no matter what the size. It could be an afternoon hiking, or a two week trip abroad. I am way too easy-going. I know how tough the daily grind can be and I am comforted by simply escaping to the outdoors. I'll probably drag you along. I am up for trying new things. I am a weekend warrior you will find me at work on a Wednesday dreaming of new gear and rivers to run. I will happily hop in the car and take off to anywhere with my daughter for the weekend. I am tanned in the summer from the sun, not a tanning bed. My constant focus will be on the joy-factor. I will always be considering the moods of the people around me and how I can help them make the most out of their days. I will turn everything into a game, make light of situations when I can, and can easily entertain a crowd. I have sea kayaked, ran white water, and has spent days hiking and canoeing. I can tie bowlines, make shelters from snow or sticks, wrap ankles, cook on a fire I built myself and make campfire coffee. I am well prepared. I knows exactly what to pack for any outing, and will rarely be found without a lighter. She carries a purse to make sure she has everything she needs with her. She always has snacks. I am not materialistic. I has spent days without air conditioning, hot showers, ovens and electricity. She has come to appreciate the comforts of everyday life. She will choose experiences over gifts. She’ll be wearing burn bracelets instead of expensive jewelry and her favourite accessory is likely a Buff. I am fiercely individual and independent. I knows what she wants and who she wants to be. She’s on a path, but she likely doesn’t know where it ends. That’s part of the adventure. She won’t need you. But she will want you. This woman will be able to take care of herself; she can cook, portage, pay her own bills, and set her own anchors. But she will love your company. I am extremely supportive.
